ike-across-ukraine</p><p>Moreover, the March attack used a total of 6 of the Russian ‘Kinzhal’ hypersonic missiles, when the previous two attacks between them had only used 1. That certainly seemed to indicate a continuing Russian commitment to the campaign. Kinzhals have a speed up to 10 times the speed of sound, making them at this time basically impossible for the Ukrainians to shoot down.</p><p>https://apnews.com/article/ukraine-russia-kinzhal-hypersonic-missiles-e0dc1e20e9dd53528c5381ca5fdee66a</p><p>The attack came as a bit of a shock in that there had been some relief that Ukraine had made it through the winter, and indeed the power situation in much of the country had actually been improving in the previous weeks. There were more and more reports that power supply was becoming less disrupted than during the winter.</p><a href="https://twitter.com/IAPonomarenko/status/1630621272446058517?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/EDb74EPeQgzxZOozCAcDK9xmBq9cNml7RKGHgE2dGQM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvSUFQb25vbWFyZW5rby5qcGc=" alt="Twitter avatar for @IAPonomarenko" loading="lazy"/>Illia Ponomarenko 🇺🇦 @IAPonomarenkoThe last day of calendar winter.
