loading="lazy"/>Alina Mykhailova @Mykhailova_A</a><video src="https://video.twimg.com/ext_tw_video/1634310860192489474/pu/vid/576x1024/w6sUYxBGomBgaWxb.mp4?tag=12" controls=""></video><a href="https://twitter.com/Mykhailova_A/status/1634310911845617664?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">9:51 PM ∙ Mar 10, 202328,263Likes2,597Retweets</a><p>Da Vinci was killed in the terrible fighting around Bakhmut, and that alone seemed to typify the nature of that struggle. It was not surprising that some doubts started to be expressed about what the Ukrainian government is attempting, including most prominently by the excellent Ukrainian journalist Illia Ponomarenko.</p><a href="https://twitter.com/IAPonomarenko/status/1634472741326802944?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/EDb74EPeQgzxZOozCAcDK9xmBq9cNml7RKGHgE2dGQM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvSUFQb25vbWFyZW5rby5qcGc=" alt="Twitter avatar for @IAPonomarenko" loading="lazy"/>Illia Ponomarenko 🇺🇦 @IAPonomarenkoI hope the Ukrainian command really, really, really knows what it’s doing in Bakhmut.</a><a href="https://twitter.com/IAPonomarenko/status/1634472741326802944?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">8:34 AM ∙ Mar 11, 202316,537Likes689Retweets</a><p>These kinds of sentiments are completely understandable, and it would be amazing were they not there. All I can say, however, is that in continuing to fight for Bakhmut, the Ukrainian government is remaining consistent in its methods of war. It is exhausting and at times leads to moments that we have seen this past week—the importance of it, however, will only be known when Ukraine goes on the offensive. The more Russia is weakened now, the better chance that offensive has to be decisive. Ukrainians are paying quite the price to make that happen.</p><p>Phillips’s Newsletter is a reader-supported publication. To receive new posts and support my work, consider becoming a free or paid subscriber.</p>